The paper deals with the complexity of solving delay games, which are two-player games of infinite duration. This topic falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and logic (cs.LO), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) due to the computational complexity of solving these games. Additionally, the paper discusses regular expressions and automata, which are topics related to formal languages (cs.FL).
